	3.
If I hadn't gone to London, I wouldn't have got this job.
If I hadn't got this job, I wouldn't have met Pauline.
If I hadn't met Pauline, I wouldn't have fallen in love.
If I hadn't fallen in love, I wouldn't have got married.
If I hadn't got married, I wouldn't have had children.
If I hadn't had children, I wouldn't have bought computer games.
If I hadn't bought computer games, I wouldn't have had an idea for a computer company.
If I hadn't had the idea for a computer company, I wouldn't have started the factory.



